cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY

This paper deals with the security implications of speculative code execution, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It specifically focuses on the use of return stack buffers (RSBs) in predicting return addresses, which relates to computer architecture (cs.AR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed attack variants also involve cross-process attacks and memory leakage, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY).
